red’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William de Kibblesworth was born about 1290, in Cramlington, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs William de Kibblesworth."},"et":{"about 1290–":"umbes 1290–Surnud","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","1337–Female":"1337–Surnud","1290–Male":"1290–Surnud","1337":"1337","about 1290":"umbes 1290","1300":"1300","about 1337":"umbes 1337","1290":"1290","Cramlington, Northumberland, England":"Cramlington, Northumberland, England","Cramlington, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Cramlington, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1290–":"noin 1290–Kuollut","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","1337–Female":"1337–Kuollut","1290–Male":"1290–Kuollut","1337":"1337","about 1290":"noin 1290","1300":"1300","about 1337":"noin 1337","1290":"1290","Cramlington, Northumberland, England":"Cramlington, Northumberland, England","Cramlington, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Cramlington, Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1290–":"environ 1290–Décédé","1300–Female":"1300–Décédée","1337–Female":"1337–Décédée","1290–Male":"1290–Décédé","1337":"1337","about 1290":"environ 1290","1300":"1300","about 1337":"environ 1337","1290":"1290","Cramlington, Northumberland, England":"Cramlington, Northumberland, Angleterre","Cramlington, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Cramlington, Northumberland, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William de Kibblesworth est né environ 1290, à Cramlington, Northumberland, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Mrs William de Kibblesworth."},"de":{"about 1290–":"um 1290–Verstorben","1300–Female":"1300–Verstorben","1337–Female":"1337–Vers